# T10.3: Implement Resource Reads

## Goal
Implement gno:// URI resource handler. CRITICAL: Reuse existing URI utilities from constants.ts.

## URI Handling (REUSE, don't reinvent)

### Use existing utilities from src/app/constants.ts:
```typescript
import { parseUri, buildUri } from '../app/constants.js';

// Normalize: parse then rebuild (handles encoded vs unencoded input)
export function normalizeGnoUri(uri: string): string {
  const parsed = parseUri(uri);  // REUSE existing
  return buildUri(parsed.collection, parsed.path);  // REUSE existing
}
```

**DO NOT create new uri.ts with parallel implementation.** The constants.ts utilities define canonical encoding rules. Any divergence creates "two canonical forms" = lookup failures.

### If constants.ts lacks parse/build:
Add them there, not in MCP layer:
```typescript
// src/app/constants.ts additions (if needed)
export function parseUri(uri: string): { collection: string; path: string } {
  const match = uri.match(/^gno:\/\/([^/]+)\/(.+)$/);
  if (!match) throw new Error(`Invalid gno:// URI: ${uri}`);
  return {
    collection: decodeURIComponent(match[1]),
    path: match[2].split('/').map(decodeURIComponent).join('/')
  };
}

export function buildUri(collection: string, path: string): string {
  const encoded = path.split('/').map(encodeURIComponent).join('/');
  return `gno://${encodeURIComponent(collection)}/${encoded}`;
}
```

## Resource Handler (src/mcp/resources/index.ts)
```typescript
import { parseUri, buildUri } from '../../app/constants.js';

function normalizeGnoUri(uri: string): string {
  const { collection, path } = parseUri(uri);
  return buildUri(collection, path);
}

export function registerResources(server: McpServer, ctx: ToolContext): void {
  // List all indexed documents as resources
  server.resource('gno://*', async () => {
    const docs = await listAllDocuments(ctx.store);
    return {
      resources: docs.map(doc => ({
        uri: buildUri(doc.collection, doc.relPath),  // REUSE
        name: doc.relPath,
        mimeType: 'text/markdown'
      }))
    };
  });

  // Read single resource with URI normalization
  server.resourceRead(async (uri) => {
    // Normalize first (handles encoded/unencoded variations)
    const canonical = normalizeGnoUri(uri);
    const { collection, path } = parseUri(canonical);

    const doc = await ctx.store.getDocumentByPath(collection, path);
    if (!doc) {
      throw new Error(`Document not found: ${uri}`);
    }

    return {
      contents: [{
        uri: canonical,
        mimeType: 'text/markdown',
        text: formatResourceContent(doc, collection, ctx.collections)
      }]
    };
  });
}
```

### Resource Content Formatting
```typescript
import path from 'node:path';  // No Bun equivalent for path utils
import { buildUri } from '../../app/constants.js';

function formatResourceContent(
  doc: Document,
  collectionName: string,
  collections: Collection[]
): string {
  const collection = collections.find(c => c.name === collectionName);
  const absPath = collection ? path.join(collection.root, doc.relPath) : doc.relPath;

  // Header comment per spec
  const header = `<!-- ${buildUri(collectionName, doc.relPath)}
     docid: #${doc.docid}
     source: ${absPath}
     mime: ${doc.mime}
-->

`;

  // Line numbers per spec (default ON for agent friendliness)
  const lines = doc.content.split('\n');
  const numbered = lines.map((line, i) => `${i + 1}: ${line}`).join('\n');

  return header + numbered;
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] **URI utilities reused from constants.ts** (not parallel implementation)
- [ ] gno:// URIs resolve to document content
- [ ] URI normalization handles encoded/unencoded input
- [ ] Content is Markdown (mirror content for non-md files)
- [ ] Header comment includes uri, docid, source, mime
- [ ] Line numbers included by default
- [ ] 404 returns standard MCP resource error
- [ ] absPath resolved from collection root

## References
- spec/mcp.md ¬ßResources - URI format, response format
- src/app/constants.ts - MUST reuse parseUri/buildUri
- src/store/types.ts - Document type
- RFC 3986 - URI encoding

