## Summary

Create new markdown document in a collection with atomic writes, path validation, and sensitive subpath protection.

## Tool Schema

```typescript
interface GnoCaptureInput {
  collection: string;    // Target collection (case-insensitive)
  content: string;       // Document content (markdown)
  title?: string;        // Optional title (for filename generation)
  path?: string;         // Optional relative path (validated)
  overwrite?: boolean;   // Default false; error on conflict
}
```

**Note**: `tags` field deferred to Tag System epic (gno-k1b).

## Response Schema

```typescript
interface GnoCaptureResult {
  docid: string;
  uri: string;
  absPath: string;
  collection: string;
  relPath: string;
  created: boolean;
  overwritten: boolean;
  serverInstanceId: string;  // For restart detection
}
```

## Path Validation

### Relative Path Rules

- No leading `/` (must be relative)
- No `..` escapes after normalization
- No NUL bytes
- Always `.md` extension (unless explicitly provided)

### Sensitive Subpath Protection

Even within valid collection roots, block writes to sensitive subdirs:

```typescript
const SENSITIVE_SUBPATHS = [
  '.ssh', '.gnupg', '.aws', '.config',
  '.git',  // Prevent repo corruption
  'node_modules',
];

function validateRelPath(p: string): string {
  const normalized = path.normalize(p);

  // Check for sensitive prefix
  const firstSegment = normalized.split(path.sep)[0];
  if (SENSITIVE_SUBPATHS.includes(firstSegment)) {
    throw new McpError('INVALID_PATH', `Cannot write to sensitive directory: ${firstSegment}`);
  }

  // ... other validations
}
```

## Implementation

```typescript
export function handleCapture(args: GnoCaptureInput, ctx: ToolContext): Promise<ToolResult> {
  return runTool(ctx, 'gno_capture', async () => {
    // Lock held for entire operation
    return withWriteLock(ctx, async () => {
      const collectionName = args.collection.toLowerCase();
      const collection = ctx.collections.find(c => c.name === collectionName);
      if (!collection) {
        throw new McpError('NOT_FOUND', `Collection: ${args.collection}`);
      }

      const relPath = args.path 
        ? validateRelPath(args.path)  // Includes sensitive subpath check
        : generateFilename(args.title, args.content);

      const absPath = path.join(collection.path, relPath);
      const exists = await Bun.file(absPath).exists();

      if (exists && !args.overwrite) {
        throw new McpError('CONFLICT', `File exists: ${relPath}`);
      }

      const fullContent = buildMarkdown(args.content, args.title);
      await atomicWrite(absPath, fullContent);

      const syncResult = await ctx.syncService.syncFiles(collection, [relPath]);

      return {
        docid: syncResult.docid,
        uri: buildUri(collectionName, relPath),
        absPath,
        collection: collectionName,
        relPath,
        created: !exists,
        overwritten: exists,
        serverInstanceId: ctx.serverInstanceId,
      };
    });
  });
}
```

## Tests

- Creates document in valid collection
- Error on sensitive subpath (.ssh, .gnupg, .git, etc)
- Error on conflict without overwrite
- Overwrites with overwrite: true
- Validates path (rejects ../, absolute, NUL)
- serverInstanceId in response
- Lock held for operation

## Acceptance

- [ ] Requires --enable-write
- [ ] Atomic writes (temp + rename)
- [ ] Write lock for operation
- [ ] Sensitive subpath protection
- [ ] serverInstanceId returned
- [ ] Standardized error codes

